  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "NES Port of \"Championship Pool\". The game is a straight-forward, virtual version of pool and includes several games: eight-ball, nine-ball, three-ball, ten-ball, fifteen-ball, straight pool (14.1 continuous), rotation, equal offense and speed pool. The player may play against the computer or up to seven other players using the same console using the \"Party Pool\" (multiplayer) option. Other gameplay modes include \"Tournament\" (single-player, computer opponents), \"Freestyle\" (players make up own game rules) and \"Challenge\" (single-player, shot practice).",
